        <updateDate>2021-12-03T17:40:47Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Strengthening Social Security Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill expands benefits, and increases specified taxes, related to the Social Security retirement and disability benefits program.</p> <p>Changes to benefits include (1) increasing the primary insurance amount for certain beneficiaries, (2) calculating cost-of-living adjustments by using a price index that tracks the spending patterns of older consumers, and (3) establishing an alternative benefit for widows or widowers in two-income households. </p> <p>Changes to taxes include phasing out the cap on earnings subject to the Social Security payroll tax. Under current law, the maximum amount subject to this tax is $142,800.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
